From 6584727e28794187a64eca49295c2dbffadef8c7 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: zzstart2 <zzstart2@example.com>
Date: Fri, 10 Apr 2026 14:48:25 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] feat(T-006): enhance QuotaData model with cost, model
 dimension, and time-series fields

Extends the quota_data statistics table to support richer analytics:

Cost dimension:
- prompt_tokens / completion_tokens (split from total token_used)
- model_ratio / completion_ratio (pricing multipliers at time of request)

Model dimension:
- channel_id (which upstream channel served the request)
- group (user group for group-level analytics)

Time-series data:
- avg_use_time / max_use_time / total_use_time (latency tracking in ms)
- stream_count (how many requests used streaming)
- error_count (failed requests within the aggregation window)

Implementation details:
- New LogQuotaDataParams struct and LogQuotaDataEx entry point for full params
- Legacy LogQuotaData preserved for backward compatibility
- Cache key extended with channel_id + group for finer-grained aggregation
- increaseQuotaData uses cross-DB-compatible CASE WHEN for max_use_time
- All RecordConsumeLog call sites updated to pass ModelRatio/CompletionRatio
- Aggregate queries (GetAllQuotaDates, GetQuotaDataGroupByUser) updated
  to include new fields with proper SUM/AVG calculations
- GORM AutoMigrate handles schema migration for all 3 DB backends
