From a1221a1577bb25dc66947b423999aee527dcadfa Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: zzstart2 <zzstart2@example.com>
Date: Fri, 10 Apr 2026 15:01:23 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] feat(T-008): add channel health check mechanism with
 real-time monitoring
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Implements per-channel health monitoring that tracks response time,
error rate, and availability from live relay traffic and periodic tests.

New files:
- model/channel_health.go: ChannelHealth persistence model (hourly buckets),
  in-memory ChannelHealthSnapshot cache, RecordChannelRequest/RecordChannelDisable
  collection APIs, FlushHealthCache for periodic DB persistence, aggregate query
  functions, CalculateHealthScore (0-100 composite score), and 30-day auto-cleanup
- controller/channel_health.go: GET /api/channel/health (overview with scoring)
  and GET /api/channel/health/:id (hourly time-series history)

Integration points:
- controller/relay.go: Record success/failure metrics in Relay() and RelayTask()
  loops via gopool.Go for zero-latency overhead on the request path
- controller/channel-test.go: Record metrics from testAllChannels periodic tests
- service/channel.go: Record disable events in DisableChannel
- main.go: Start RunHealthDataFlusher background goroutine (same interval as
  DataExportInterval, default 5 min)
- model/main.go: Register ChannelHealth in both migrateDB and migrateDBFast
- router/api-router.go: Wire health endpoints under /api/channel (AdminAuth)

Design decisions:
- Write-through cache pattern: hot path writes only to in-memory map (mutex-locked),
  background flusher merges to DB every N minutes — zero DB pressure per request
- Hourly time buckets for storage efficiency while preserving trend granularity
- Aggregate queries use cross-DB-safe SQL (no CAST AS FLOAT, COALESCE for NULLs,
  GROUP BY channel_id only with MAX for denormalized name/type)
- Health score: 40pt error rate + 30pt latency + 30pt availability = 100
